en_563659_0	Army Boxers who recently championed in the reputed ‘Clifford Cup’ tournament winning 6 Gold, 5 Silver and 4 Bronze medals after absence of 7 years were feted and congratulated by the Commander of the Army, Lieutenant General Shavendra Silva after having invited them to the Army Headquarters on Tuesday (15).
en_563659_1	The tournament, challenged by many island-wide boxing teams for this prestigious ‘Clifford Cup’ got underway at Royal MAS Boxing Arena during 7-11 October and the finals were held on Friday (11).
en_563659_2	Boxers in the Army Sports Club defeating the Slimline Boxing hegemony after consecutive seven years secured the Championship in the 93rd ‘Clifford Cup’ Boxing Tournament in a convincing manner.
en_563659_3	Lance Corporal M.P.G.N Sajeewa Nuwan of 6 Sri Lanka Armoured Corps (SLAC) winning the 49 kg weight class was adjudged the Best Boxer, an unbroken record he made for the third time in National Boxing Tournaments.
en_563659_4	Earlier, he was the Best Boxer in the Layton Cup Boxing Championship and also in the National Boxing Championship in the year 2018.
en_563659_5	Army Boxers throughout the tournament shone prominently posing a formidable challenge to their rivals, amid roars of applause.
en_563659_6	In the women’s category for the Dian Gomes Challenge Trophy, Lance Corporal H.S Priyadarshani of 3 (Volunteer) Sri Lanka Army Women’s Corps (SLAWC) was rated as the Best female Looser.
en_563659_7	On the final day, Mr Dian Gomes, Chairman, Sri Lanka Boxing Association gave away the Championship trophy to Lance Corporal M.P.G.N Sajeewa Nuwan of the Army and other achievers.
en_563659_8	During Tuesday (15) morning’s interactive meeting with the Commander of the Army, those Boxers had the distinguished chance of sharing a few thoughts with the Army Chief who profusely praised them and talked high of their achievements.
en_563659_9	In appreciation, Lieutenant General Shavendra Silva gifted each of them with a memento and extended his best wishes for their future endeavours.
en_563659_10	Major General Anura Sudasinghe, Director General Sports and Colonel Dinesh Udugama, Colonel Genral Staff at Directorate of Operations were also present during the meeting at the Commander’s office.
